{"id": "1413968764541735066", "channel_id": "1402538040253087766", "type": 0, "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "author_bot": false, "content": "okay so... In part 3 of Horla's story, does anyone else find it narratively confusing that the entire time we've been trying to get to \"Medici Avenue\" (美第奇 大道) to meet with our contact, but once we arrive we're suddenly talking about \"March Street\" (三月街)?\n\n> \"Excuse me, could you tell me how to get to Medici Avenue?\"\n> \"Let's go to Medici Avenue and find the contact for investigation.\"\n> \"Excuse me, does this bus go to Medici Avenue?\"\n\n> Bright light from an unknown source illuminates the roof and tables of the roadside café.\n> \"I remember reading in the newspaper that March Street was originally an ordinary street, but it gained fame because a painter created a piece for this café.\n> I really love this story and once wrote a poem about it. In the poem, the artist eventually settled at No. 99, End of March Street.\n> I think it's not that March Street encountered the painter, but rather that the painter encountered March Street.\"\n> \"The contact is at 101 March Street. Get ready, let's go.\"\n\nNot to mention this line:\n> CN ingame: `三月街……没有101号。`\n> GTL CN: `Sān yuè jiē……méiyǒu 101 hào.`\n> GTL EN: `March Street...there is no No. 101.`\n> EN ingame: `San Yue Street... There is no No. 101.`\n\nso... is this some italian geography thing I'm too american to understand? or...?", "timestamp": "2025-09-06T19:27:03.736000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1413969475803283518", "channel_id": "1402538040253087766", "type": 0, "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "author_bot": false, "content": "I get that it's possible we were trying to get to a lesser-known road (March St.) so we've been asking for directions to a major adjacent or cross-road (Medici Ave.), but that just seems odd to me.", "timestamp": "2025-09-06T19:29:53.314000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
